Feature: Epic readiness guardrail

  Scenario: Epic must have child issues before moving to ready
    Given the issue type is "epic"
    When transitioning from "in_progress" to "open"
    Then warn "Create at least one child story or task before moving an epic to ready."
    Then explain "Epics represent milestones composed of multiple child issues."
    Then suggest "If this is a single deliverable, represent it as a story or task instead of an epic."
    Then the issue must have at least 1 child issue
